com.polarion.alm.shared.api.model

Interface ModelObjectsSearch<T extends ModelObject>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, IterableWithSize<T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ModelObjectsSearchWithTemplates<T>

    public interface ModelObjectsSearch<T extends ModelObject>
extends IterableWithSize<T>
    This interface acts both as builder for Lucene search and iterable of the result. So it it can be used in way: for(WorkItem wi: transaction.workItems().search().query("my query")){... The iterator never returns null values. All search parameters (which are specified using methods like query(String) are optional. There is special caching in place (historical-queries-sizes in EHCache) for the count of objects matching the historical queries (the one where the baseline revision is not null), so calling only the IterableWithSize.size() in these cases is much faster than iterating over the items.
    Since:
    3.9.0
